11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §2423-F, sub-§8, as repealed and replaced by PL 2019, c. 331,
13 §17 and amended by PL 2021, c. 669, §5, is further amended to read:
14 8. Registration requirements. This subsection governs registration requirements of
15 a manufacturing facility or a person authorized to engage in cannabis extraction using
16 inherently hazardous substances under subsection 3 and the officer or director or assistant
17 of the facility or person.
18 A. In accordance with rules adopted under subsection 10, the department shall register
19 and issue a registration certificate with a registry identification number to a
20 manufacturing facility or a person authorized to engage in cannabis extraction within
21 30 days to the facility or person if the facility or person provides:
22 (1) The annual fee required pursuant to section 2425‑A, subsection 10;
23 (2) The legal name of the facility or person and, if incorporated, evidence of
24 incorporation and evidence that the corporation is in good standing with the
25 Secretary of State;
26 (3) The physical address of the facility or person or the physical address where an
27 applicant who is an individual will engage in the activities authorized under this
28 section. If the facility or person changes its physical location, or if a person
29 registered under this subsection changes the location at which the person engages
30 in activities authorized under this section, the facility or person shall notify the
31 department of the new location; and
32 (4) The name, address and date of birth of each officer or director of the facility
33 or person.
34 B. In accordance with rules adopted under subsection 10, the department shall issue
35 registry identification cards to the officer or director or assistant of a registered
