22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment removes the provision of the bill that increases the current limit under
2244 the medical cannabis laws to allow a caregiver to cultivate up to 60 mature cannabis plants,
2255 up to 120 immature cannabis plants, up to 1,000 square feet of mature plant canopy and up
2266 to 2,000 square feet of immature plant canopy. The amendment also extends the registration
2277 period for manufacturing facilities and for persons authorized to engage in cannabis
2288 extraction using inherently hazardous substances from one year to 2 years. The amendment
2299 updates the requirement for the Department of Administrative and Financial Services to
3300 conduct criminal history record checks for an officer or director or assistant of a registered
3311 manufacturing facility or person authorized to engage in cannabis extraction using
3322 inherently hazardous substances from annually to every 2 years and makes other necessary
3333 technical changes. The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
3344 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3355 (See attached)
